.TH "of_dma_router_xlate" 9 "of_dma_router_xlate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_router_xlate \- translation function for router devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dma_chan *" of_dma_router_xlate
.BI "(struct of_phandle_args *dma_spec "  ","
.BI "struct of_dma *ofdma "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dma_spec" 12
pointer to DMA specifier as found in the device tree
.IP "ofdma" 12
pointer to DMA controller data (router information)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function creates new dma_spec to be passed to the router driver's
\fBof_dma_route_allocate\fP function to prepare a dma_spec which will be used
to request channel from the real DMA controller.
